PlayerScout | Player Development on Instagram: &quot;Comment 20 below:&#x2060;
&#x2060;
Most players don&#x2019;t fall behind because of talent.&#x2060;
They fall behind because they don&#x2019;t know how to reset.&#x2060;
&#x2060;
You can train hard all week.&#x2060;
&#x2060;
You can do extra sessions.&#x2060;
You can put in more effort than everyone else.&#x2060;
&#x2060;
But the game doesn&#x2019;t reward effort.&#x2060;
&#x2060;
It rewards what you do&#x2060;
after something goes wrong.&#x2060;
&#x2060;
After the mistake.&#x2060;
After the bad touch.&#x2060;
After the moment your confidence drops.&#x2060;
&#x2060;
That&#x2019;s where most players lose control.&#x2060;
&#x2060;
They carry it into the next action.&#x2060;
Then the next one.&#x2060;
Then the whole game is gone.&#x2060;
&#x2060;
The players who move forward are different.&#x2060;
&#x2060;
They don&#x2019;t avoid mistakes.&#x2060;
They recover faster from them.&#x2060;
&#x2060;
They reset quickly.&#x2060;
They refocus.&#x2060;
They get back into the game.&#x2060;
&#x2060;
Same player.&#x2060;
Different response.&#x2060;
&#x2060;
That&#x2019;s the difference you see on the pitch.&#x2060;
&#x2060;
If your child struggles with this, or you notice their confidence drop during games, this is the part that needs fixing.&#x2060;
